net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class Field

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Field
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, LocaleContextSource, Component, Editable, ListCellRenderer, TableCellEditor, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleEntryField, LocalizedObjectKeyFieldComponent

    @Configurable
@UIElement(supportsAction=true,
           name="field")
public class Field
extends ComponentImpl
implements Editable, TableCellRenderer, TableCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, ListCellRenderer

    The Field allows the user to enter text with the keyboard.

    This component may be used as a table cell renderer and editor, tree cell renderer and editor, and list cell renderer. The appropriate cell renderer/editor method must be called to behave correctly as a table cell renderer/editor.

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called when a Component is first attached to a WindowManager. This means the Component should have valid return values from getApplication(), getLocaleContext(), getParent(). It is preferable to have all construction of the Component go here since a valid LocaleContext, Application object, etc., are available.

        When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class init(). init() is called only once for each Component. The parent component will have been init()ed before init() is called.

        NOTE: Do not call this method from application code. It is meant to be called by the WindowManager only.

        Specified by:
        init in interface Component
        Overrides:
        init in class ComponentImpl

        Allow the component to process any form fields before rendering. This method must be called by subclasses.
